<subSubSection lastPageId="230" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
<pageBreakToken pageId="229" pageNumber="230" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 199" captionStartId="F199" captionText="Figure 199. Distribution of Conostegia trichosantha." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure199" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96557" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">199</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Panama where it grows mostly in cloud forests, 250-1250 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974057" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure199" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96557" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" start="Figure 199" startId="F199">
<paragraph pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Figure 199.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Conostegia trichosantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="230" pageNumber="231">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="230" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="230" pageNumber="231">
<pageBreakToken pageId="230" pageNumber="231" start="start">Conostegia</pageBreakToken>
trichosantha
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very distinctive species because of its dense indument of smooth hairs, small leaves with very plinerved and usually asymmetric venation, pseudolateral, short inflorescences, 5-merous flowers with narrow and acute white petals and very exserted styles. It is perhaps not surprising that in the molecular phylogeny, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="230" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="230" pageNumber="231">Conostegia trichosantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears as closely related to other Panamanian endemics such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jefensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="230" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="230" pageNumber="231">Conostegia jefensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia peltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="230" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="230" pageNumber="231">Conostegia peltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as with the more widespread 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia consimilis" order="Myrtales" pageId="230" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="230" pageNumber="231">Conostegia consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. With these taxa it shares narrow petals and with most of them angulate seeds with verruculose angles. This species accumulates water in the hypanthium indument.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
